### ============================
### TUS resumable uploads (demo)
### ============================
### Companion to the blog post:
### "Resumable file uploads with TUS and Jakarta EE"
###
### The TUS core protocol in three requests: POST creates the upload,
### HEAD returns the current offset, PATCH appends bytes at that offset.
### Every request/response carries Tus-Resumable: 1.0.0.
###
### After the POST, copy the id from the Location header into the
### requests below (or use a real TUS client - it does this for you).

### 0. Capability discovery
OPTIONS http://localhost:8080/api/tus
Tus-Resumable: 1.0.0

### 1. Create an upload (declares the total size in bytes)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tus
Tus-Resumable: 1.0.0
Upload-Length: 34

### 2. Upload the first chunk (17 bytes), starting at offset 0
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/tus/{id}
Tus-Resumable: 1.0.0
Upload-Offset: 0
Content-Type: application/offset+octet-stream

FIRST-HALF-BYTES-

### 3. Ask where to resume from (returns Upload-Offset: 17)
HEAD http://localhost:8080/api/tus/{id}
Tus-Resumable: 1.0.0

### 4. Resume: upload the rest from offset 17
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/tus/{id}
Tus-Resumable: 1.0.0
Upload-Offset: 17
Content-Type: application/offset+octet-stream

SECOND-HALF-BYTES

### 5. Wrong offset -> 409 Conflict with the correct Upload-Offset
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/tus/{id}
Tus-Resumable: 1.0.0
Upload-Offset: 1
Content-Type: application/offset+octet-stream

WILL-BE-REJECTED
